                            <comment id="475098" author="ssmirnov" created="Wed, 15 Oct 2025 20:56:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Interesting: it looks like client1 on trevis-29vm1&#160; comes up with an IPv4-based NID:&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Added LNI 10.240.38.180@tcp [8/256/0/180]&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yet later it is trying to establish a connection to an IPv6 destination:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
00000400:00000100:1.0:1759824457.913916:0:239950:0:(acceptor.c:109:lnet_connect_console_error()) Connection to fd33:3981:3213:f020:0:5254:a2:6f9c@tcp at host [fd33:3981:3213:f020:0:5254:a2:6f9c]:7988 was refused: check that Lustre is running on that node.&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This doesn&apos;t work, which is probably correct (because we&apos;re trying to connect IPv4 and IPv6 endpoints):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
(socklnd_cb.c:976:ksocknal_launch_packet()) No usable routes to 12345-fd33:3981:3213:f020:0:5254:a2:6f9c@tcp&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
